===Conjunction===
'''or'''
# Connects at least two [[word]]s, [[phrase]]s, [[clause]]s, [[etc.]] that each could make a [[sentence]] [[true]].  In [[English]], this is the "[[inclusive or]]."  The "[[exclusive or]]" is "[[either...or]]".
# Logical union of two [[set]]s of values.  There are two forms, an [[exclusive or]] and an [[inclusive or]].

====Synonyms====
*[[and/or]]

====See also====
*[[neither...nor]]

